<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="36.[189,310,400,426]" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[188,1399,447,614]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="De Oliveira &amp; Brescovit, 2021" authorityName="De Oliveira &amp; Brescovit" authorityYear="2021" box="[298,439,447,473]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Tafana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruizi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[298,439,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Tafana ruizi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[446,536,448,474]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="AMNH" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[755,900,448,473]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Tafana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="straminea">
<emphasis box="[755,900,448,473]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">T. straminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="De Oliveira &amp; Brescovit, 2021" authorityName="De Oliveira &amp; Brescovit" authorityYear="2021" box="[956,1137,447,473]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Tafana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kunturmarqa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[956,1137,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">T. kunturmarqa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1144,1234,448,474]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having the base of the embolus large and inclined, but differ by having the ventral tegular process large and apex of tegulum not rounded (
<figureCitation box="[479,586,518,544]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1785,1811]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,458,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-195@37.[189,1399,458,1743]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 21. Tafana ruizi sp. nov. (A, C–E =holotype, ♂, IBSP 258183; B, E–F =paratype, ♀, IBSP 258183). A. Habitus, dorsal view.B. Habitus, dorsal view.C. Left palp, ventral view (arrow indicating the base of the embolus). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, dorsal view. F. Epigynum, ventral view. G. Vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: A = atrium; ABE= apophysis of base of the embolus; CD =copulatory ducts; CO =copulatory opening; E =embolus; FD =fertilization ducts; H =hood; LL= lateral lobes; MA =median apophysis; RTA=retrolateral tibial apophysis; S1=primary spermathecae; S2 = secondary spermathecae; T =tegulum. Scale bars: A–B=3.5 mm; C=0.5 mm; D–G =0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4655467" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4655467/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 21C</figureCitation>
). Females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="AMNH" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[921,1066,519,544]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Tafana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="straminea">
<emphasis box="[921,1066,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">T. straminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="De Oliveira &amp; Brescovit, 2021" authorityName="De Oliveira &amp; Brescovit" authorityYear="2021" box="[1122,1302,518,544]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Tafana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kunturmarqa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1122,1302,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">T. kunturmarqa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1309,1399,518,544]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having the atrial septum, but differ by having the wide atrium, showing the copulation openings and hood long and circular (
<figureCitation box="[469,613,588,614]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1785,1811]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,458,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-195@37.[189,1399,458,1743]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 21. Tafana ruizi sp. nov. (A, C–E =holotype, ♂, IBSP 258183; B, E–F =paratype, ♀, IBSP 258183). A. Habitus, dorsal view.B. Habitus, dorsal view.C. Left palp, ventral view (arrow indicating the base of the embolus). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, dorsal view. F. Epigynum, ventral view. G. Vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: A = atrium; ABE= apophysis of base of the embolus; CD =copulatory ducts; CO =copulatory opening; E =embolus; FD =fertilization ducts; H =hood; LL= lateral lobes; MA =median apophysis; RTA=retrolateral tibial apophysis; S1=primary spermathecae; S2 = secondary spermathecae; T =tegulum. Scale bars: A–B=3.5 mm; C=0.5 mm; D–G =0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4655467" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4655467/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs 21F–G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[625,678,588,614]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="57.[187,230,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,495,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-161@57.[189,1398,495,1783]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="Fig. 33. Female genitalia, digested. A. Tafana huatanay sp. nov. (MUSM). B. Tafana ruizi sp. nov. (IBSP 258183). C. Tafana silhavyi (Caporiacco, 1955) (MNHN). D. Tafana maracay sp. nov. (MNHN 11314). E. Tafana arawak sp. nov. (MNHN 11320). F. Tafana pittieri sp. nov. (AMNH). G. Tafana oliviae sp. nov. (MCZ). H. Tafana orinoco sp. nov. (MIZA 07062). Abbreviations: CD =copulatory ducts; FD =fertilization ducts; H =hood; S1 =primary spermathecae; S2 =secondary spermathecae. Scale bars: A–H =0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4655511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4655511/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">33B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="36.[189,324,654,680]" box="[189,324,654,680]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,654,680]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,654,680]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Etymology</emphasis>
